      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 58,
      "message": "Thank you for fixing the variable names. However, you misunderstood my comment on the code change though:\n\nThis set of lines:\n        if \"tnxEnabled\" in ctx.node.properties:\n            tnxEnabled = ctx.node.properties[\"tnxEnabled\"]\n        else:\n            tnxEnabled= False\ncan be replaced with the >>single<< line:\n\n       tnx_enabled = ctx.node.properties.get(\"tnxEnabled\", False)\n \nsimplifying the code and reducing the size.\n\nSimilar, for replication_case and the others, you get this (.get() already returns None if the value is not in the dictionary):\n\n        topic_description = ctx.node.properties.get(\"topic_description\")\n        replication_case = ctx.node.properties.get(\"replication_case\")\n        global_mr_url = ctx.node.properties.get(\"global_mr_url\")\n        use_existing = ctx.node.properties.get(\"useExisting\", False)",
      "author": {
